      <div xml:id="NA96-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi talaivikku uraippāḷāy (ET: talaimakaṉai) varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante asked for marriage as one who is talking to HER while HE is behind the hedge.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA96">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            ituvē, naṟuvī ñāḻaṉ māmalar tāayp</l>
<l>            puṉṉait tatainta veṇmaṇa loruciṟaip</l>
<l>            putuvatu puṇarnta {pūmali} poḻilē</l>
<l>            yutuvē, pommaṟ paṭutirai nammō ṭāṭip</l>
<l>            puṟantāḻ piruḷiya piṟaṅku kuralaim </l>
<l>            pālvariṉ kuruḷiya {tūnīrt} tuṟaiyē</l>
<l>            yatuvē, koṭuṅkaḻai nivanta neṭuṅkā ṉeyta</l>
<l>            lampakai neṟittaḻai yaṇipeṟat taiit</l>
<l>            tamiyar ceṉṟa kāṉa leṉṟāaṅ</l>
<l>            kuḷḷutō ṟuḷḷutō ṟurukip </l>
<l>            paiip paiyap pacantaṉai pacappē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>“This [is] the grove {abounding in flowers} where we newly united,</l>
<l rend="indent">on one wing of the white sand dense around the Puṉṉai tree</l>
<l rend="indent2">spread with big blossoms of the Ñāḻal with fragrant flowers.</l>
<l>Over there [is] the ghat {with pure water} where [he] curled,</l>
<l rend="indent4">when he came,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">pālvariṉ kuruḷiya</term>: this variant is neither metrically nor syntactically very satisfactory (we would expect something like <term xml:lang="ta">aimpāl / varunar</term>), but the printed version with its strange <term xml:lang="ta">tuvariṉar</term> ("where he who had coral(?) was graceful/considerate with [my] five-fold [hair]...") is likewise unsatisfactory.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">the five parts of [my] full-grown tufts [of hair] that were dark</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] hung down on [my] back when playing with us</l>
<l rend="indent3">in the thick inrolling waves.</l>
<l>That [is] the seashore grove where he had gone on his own,</l>
<l rend="indent">knitting, to obtain a decoration, calyxes [and] foliage in pretty contrast</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the long-stalked blue waterlily that came up by the bent bamboo.”</l>
<l rend="indent4">As if speaking thus<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">āṅku</term>, the usual particle of comparison does not seem to make sense here, and T.V.G. takes it as an expletive used to complete the metrical foot (which is not overly convincing, since <term xml:lang="ta">eṉṟu</term> often enough does count for a full foot).</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">whenever whenever you remember, melting,</l>
<l>you have gently gently succumbed to pallor.</l>
        </lg>
